A new era of crisis begins.
The France and the rest of Europe are in investors' sights.
A statistical tornado passed over Europe on Tuesday.
Each of the states has published GDP information for the 3A.
The Czech economy stagnated in the last quarter, while France and Germany are growing.
The bond market is breaking all records.
Investors are not only looking at Italy, but also at Spain, France, Austria and others.
