Iranian students are willing to die for their country's nuclear program.
They created a human shield
A few hundred college students have created a human shield around a nuclear site in Iran.
With this gesture, they want to support their country's nuclear program in the face of a possible Israeli assault.
The students began to pray at noon in front of the site and then wished for the death of the US and Israel.
A few hundred students from Isfahan universities created a human shield Tuesday around the Isfahan nuclear technology center where uranium is processed.
They have openly expressed that they will defend their country's nuclear agenda at the risk of their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) noted in its latest information that Iran has not stopped strengthening its nuclear weapons.
There are reports in Israel of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
The students began to pray at noon in front of the site and then wished for the death of the US and Israel.
In the event of an attack, the objective of which would be to destroy Iran's nuclear program, the targets would be not only Isfahan, but also the Natanz site where uranium is enriched.
The diet of an obese child: does not eat breakfast and takes cold cuts for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have problems with overweight, 9% of schoolchildren are an above average weight and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families that have an unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows once again how important is the environment in which human beings evolve and the models that surround them.
On the tables of obese children we find, for example, deli meats 50% more often than in families of children of normal weight.
19% of obese people had fries at dinner according to the survey conducted with an awareness action "Obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of the little fat people sport is also not a habit, which is now the case for most schoolchildren today - only 15% answered that at least once a week parents find time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and involved 900 primary school students in the Czech Republic.
This was the second edition of "Obesity is not a coincidence", an action supported by the General Health Insurance and the company Unilever.
Since the beginning, more than 12,000 students from sixth to third grade have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of overweight or even obese children is the lack of a correct diet and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half of the children questioned indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast-in case - lunch - snack - dinner, which is one of the basic principles of a good diet," says one of the results of the survey.
Without breakfast and cold cuts at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that to have a healthy development it takes some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In Czechia, only 23% of students' families eat at the same time.
In most families everyone has breakfast alone.
And the worst that has been noted is that a tenth of the population does not eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is however the basis of a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that families of obese children are more often consumed unhealthy fries.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks sugary drinks every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children interviewed play sports regularly but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare your diet
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food from possibilities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating."
Among their favorite dishes there are many cakes, meats and sweets.
"The most alarming is in particular a strong preference for sweet lemonades," the survey results stated.
For lunch, pasta took first place just ahead of white meat.
The children did not want starchy foods at all and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Focus on health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the moment they receive the relevant information.
"During a control of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session "Obesity is not a coincidence", there was a determined desire to move towards a healthy diet," indicate the results of the survey.
The most striking was for example with regard to sweet lemonades, as children began to give preference to drinking water.
Children most often ticked on the questionnaire white meat and fish as the main course and would reduce sweet dishes and "knedliky" (Czech specialty of bread flour or potato balls).
The stylist must also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In a blurb article about how stylists learn how to learn, I got a little angry that there were a lot of them from the beginning.
I didn't think about what would happen next.
Presentations by three professionals of the specialty, the clothing of the characters and a seminar on what happens on site.
And it will be worse.
The closer we get to the final exams, the more practical exercises and information await us.
And even when there are classes on Saturdays and Sundays it is really "stuffed".
This time we dealt with the director Alenka (during the course there are no boys) how to dress the woman who does not have standard measurements.
And women of this type are the majority.
One has a small neck, the other a boy's body, without any particular curve, another overweight.
The stylist must know how to optically amplify wide arms, extend a neck or add necessary curves.
We were able to emphasize the character nicely and also not to dress too conspicuously types of women like Jennifer Lopez with a strong chest and pronounced hips and a thin waist.
For example, if there is a difference between the waist and the hips in such a way that skirts or trousers do not fit at all, it is worth having it customized.
And you will not regret it because the clothing that falls impeccably is priceless.
In a custom-made skirt you will feel much better than in one that slips constantly, rolls up and does not hold on to the belt and so on.
For those who have a masculine appearance can afford a Tucker style clothing, with pieces of fabric sewn, or even embroidery.
There are obviously many examples of various appearances and I am glad that I have all week to sort through all the information received.
But I'm also afraid that considering what I have to do at home there will be too much.
Each trainee was given a celebrity to dress for the day and evening.
We must take into consideration the current appearance, the fashion type of the personality as well as its appearance.
I will have to "dress" Miranda Kerr, who you may know from the Secret of Victoria campaign.
Deep down, it makes me happy, because it's better than dressing Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera who has gained almost a hundred pounds lately (please don't take my statement completely seriously) or the young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut and sew from magazines or search the internet, print and work on graphics.
The Moodboard, as we say for the final result, expresses our personal style as well as our relationship with graphic design.
Also thinking about the graphic part of styling is also important.
The stylist does not only dress the physical but creates for example the productive pages in magazines (on given products trends for handbags, coats, etc ...).
Mario Kamenik, stylist and graphic designer, talked to us about all this.
But this,... until Sunday
The stylist must have a general vision
Three guests from the specialty gave a diverse look to Saturday's session filled with information about the different types of characters.
Honza Pokorny, stylist, Jakub Polanka fashion designer and Ben Renc, fashion photographer.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should know how to use it.
And a talented stylist knows how to work with one piece of clothing in a different way.
Variability is essential for this example.
Like for example this trench coat which must be worn in a classic way with jeans and a t-shirt as a light coat but also it can also dress the naked body, with pumps and take a picture of it like a dress.
Or just roll up the sleeves or collar and immediately have a new look.
"Play with that," he stressed.
But I particularly appreciated the following advice: "For work you need to know the rules perfectly".
"You can then start violating it," Jakub said.
Finally I understand why we try to learn these rules, what to do with them, to what, why, while in fashion magazines we sometimes see something else.
No statements on fashion shows.
I know again, thanks to fashion photographer Ben, that the stylist must have many more variations of clothing than those that are photographed.
That is to say that for fashion story which will have about ten pages (so a dozen models) I must be ready to "resize" at least fifteen of them.
And also, a garment and its combination with other elements appear completely differently than in reality.
We have to reckon with this during a template creation.
The fact that image and style sometimes make half the success was confirmed to us by Honza Pokorny.
Just look at Madonna who is not a great singer but her image and marketing have made her a global star.
In the Czech Republic, the approach towards the use of stylists' services is still cautious.
And familiar faces sometimes consider them useless (it is enough that I know something but what I seem passes in second place).
And if someone gets a styling done by us, then we have to rely on the fact that he dictates to us with a high probability a completely different size (smaller) than the one he actually has.
We then have to browse google and make sure if the boulevard news reports the celebrity in question, if she has lost weight or gained weight etc ...
Honza and Mario asked us on Sunday on the heart that it is not enough for the stylist to orient himself in fashion and know how to assemble models.
He must communicate with the people he dresses and it is therefore important to be a good psychologist.
Know how to guess people, not flatter yourself, keep your opinion.
"When a manager asks you to sort through her cupboard and fill it with new items you can't throw it all away and say, My God what a horror."
"You'll find a few things that you'll find pretty and he you'll advise on what to wear them with," Mario says.
He showed us concretely what must contain everything called the "placovka" or stylist's bag.
It's the one you hang around your waist and carry with you for everything you need.
In addition to clearly defined things such as scissors, hair removal rollers or nurse pins, there is also nylon thread (which the stylist uses to photograph products such as bags, or hats), special clips with which a garment is closed in the back, if it is too large (the pin or other type of staple are not usable because they could damage the garment) or a sewing kit.
So that we are not only people who listen but who have tried something in a practical way they have taught us how to properly resow shoes.
And during the photo shoot in the workshop where the surface is equal, the sole could be damaged, especially outside.
And so we glued and pasted.
We were not allowed to touch the scissors so as not to inadvertently hurt ourselves.
So you really need skills.
Mario made me happy when he congratulated me on my creation.
The account I am reporting is not for my girlfriend.
This is just a small summary of what we learned during the second class weekend.
I am beginning to understand more and more that making styling a profession is not a walk in a rose garden, let everyone say what they want.
The need for speed The Run is contested throughout America.
Revision
Originally a trouble-free race turns into a routine morning trip to work because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who don't care.
To a certain extent, this fulfills everyone's ambition, but it is useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new part subtitled The Run has produced high expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already aged Need for Speed racing series and release a kind of game from playable games that wouldn't just be counted with points.
So we were curious how will be the added passages during which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole thing pulls down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of an incomprehensible laziness on the part of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught up in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them starts participating in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the West Coast in San Francisco and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than 50 races.
As a result, each race is done on a different route and the planned stages in different environments that stand out quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also quite pretty even if the graphic technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
Well, it's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snow-capped mountains is very visually pleasing.
The tests are also occasionally embellished with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Besides that the different races are well arranged one behind the other.
There are only a small number but that is enough.
There are moments you strive to surpass the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classic duel with the stopwatch) and then again awaits you another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and try to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty are the passages out of vehicle.
It is more of an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is good like that because this element is not likely to hinder and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that currently there is nothing extraordinary but we can not say that it is negative.
As for the realistic simulation you will have to look elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is ok.
Problems begin to appear after some time.
In contrast to the driving model, that of collisions is not yet developed.
We don't expect complicated warping and collisions from this game, but when you don't have any idea how your car behaves when colliding with any object, it's not completely good.
During tight overtaking you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car goes into crazy aerobatics.
Or ends up in tatters.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done so that when you have broken your face or you have gone out in the scenery the game takes you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 reboots.
When you have used the 5 reboots you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really rely on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and you have to find the solution by remembering from memory the piece of route in question.
The big problem with this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example there are certain turns that must be passed in a certain way otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you meet on a given place "civilian" vehicles always in the same configuration whether you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds early or one minute late.
What angers you are the situations when you easily see the opponent pass between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and conture them or brake.
It is equal if you go in front of him because it is "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation he always arrives very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
During the whole time of the game, you, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent who precedes you in the same place.
This annoys the most at the end of the game when you drive on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at all costs pass in front of you.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a good number of times.
It is understandable that the goal of this game is to do something captivating and full of adredaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and the places with so much action that you do not have time to follow everything that happens.
And it is equal if it is because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there is no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is the change of car during the races.
You have to pay attention to the gas pumps on the routes because you can change cars however most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American engines for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic finery on highly technical driving for example on winding roads in the mountains.
And the challenge mode, which are races in particular places that you know from the adventure, goes very well with the main regime of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that are added to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog function which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult blows to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speedometer tells you between 150 and 200 km/hour (a priori) and behind you arrives a metro train that sends the car directly to the scrap yard.
At the editors we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about it when creating this game or if the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally nice and in some cases really great.
What is disturbing is that in more extreme situations, the imagery does not hold up and in some cases tragically.
This especially concerns accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is your choice.
In order to please as many people as possible and especially the most young audiences, a new soundtrack has been created in the style "I mix everything", but we can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Overall impression of Need for Speed: So the Run is really confusing.
If the game didn't have these stupid mistakes we could safely say that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game feels like it's not finished.
The fun is really good but be prepared for mistakes to hit you in the eye with the force of an aerodrome reflector.
Les Etudiants de velours in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from higher schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is formed by two concerts organized on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the festival committee sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir of high schools and secondary classes which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening takes place the concert "Velvet Students" in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of the Charles University perform.
The Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate with dignity the International Day of Students and recall the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public choir music of the highest level and develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Choirs in cooperation with the Jan Kepler Gymnasium.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
In addition to high-level concerts, the program offers msical meetings, a student happening and other activities.
Those interested will find all the information on the internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negativists and eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
"I didn't expect such a tough war."
"It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all the players get used to their new role", this is how Miléna Vicenova began her presentation at the Faculty of Law the Czech Ambassador to the European Union.
When she managed to describe the various EU bodies and their relations in such an understandable and visible way, to the point that many lecturers at Charles University's Faculty of Law might envy her, she showed how seriously she takes her motto "understandable and openly about Europe".
Ms Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new Permanent President of the European Council.
"From the beginning there was criticism that he is bland, that he is a leather-ring, that he cannot take over any mission and I must say that he took everyone's breath away because he plays his role perfectly."
"He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take Europe."
She explained the new post of High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy in response to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "What telephone number should I call?", so as an important step towards the unity and greater clarity of the Union's policy towards states, such as China or India.
Nobody wants to ban us from our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also referred to the agenda that the European Council has lived, is living and will live in the near future.
She described the Czech Presidency of two years ago as a success.
The Czechs solved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or organised an Eastern Partnership Summit.
She described the fall of the government as very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, "activity has been in full swing" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved even now.
In addition, the Union's new seven-month budget, which is becoming very complicated because of the current economic situation, must be approved.
As it would seem that the budget will be thin and with a view to savings, which branch will have priority, which countries will receive the most aid, the least, everything has to be resolved in the context of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
"I really don't like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that nobody understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels nobody makes round or twisted pickles, bananas that are differentially large or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky".
She wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the EU institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador, the Czechs have the reputation of being Eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect rather than positively.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
According to her, the fault is the result of several factors, such as the timidity of our candidates, their inability to write a cover letter and weak support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech Presidency, she then stressed the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me: 'Hey, what are you doing there, what else is this Visegrad group doing?' And he's not happy at all."
According to Vicenova, in the near future new tough rules on fiscal policy await member countries.
It is the concept of a two-speed, if not multi-speed, Europe that prevails rather than a 'new European Federation'.
"We have countries in the eurozone and others outside the zone."
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute for Enhanced Cooperation."
In the first place it was said that countries that want it cooperate with each other and those that do not want to stay in their corner."
"There will be many such institutes and there will be a truly two-speed Europe," Vicenova said.
From this point of view, she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis on which all issues having an impact on the EU should be debated between all EU members and not only the members of the eurozone.
History of a brand:
IBM innovator begins second century of existence
If someone were to look for the word that most closely expresses the IBM strategy, the closest would be "the long term".
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has passed a hundred years.
The foundation for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm's first CEO, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left the slogan that many global problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
Its slogan "THINK'!" has become the imprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began to publish in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson's carefully crafted company culture.
For us, IBM means long-term thinking of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it always remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change everyone else around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more," said the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano for the anniversary.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the thirties, began to look after his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - the IBM people were the only ones among the first American employees to have paid vacation, employer-paid insurance plus a stylish employee uniform and a well-developed system of rewards for inventors and traders.
In the same way, IBM has a well-developed system of relationships with the customer.
The company was initially brilliant at discovering talent – as one of the first firms to abolish all forms of discrimination and thus could have a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been with IBM for thirty years and currently holds the position of Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has been doing what is called jamy, online brainstorming from which a lot of future strategies and innovations have emerged.
It is no wonder that he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people working.
An institution with a good name
It is the internal and external image of the company that ensures it a secure position in the field of business.
"From the beginning, IBM had a concept more of an institution than a technology firm," said Rosabeth Moss Kanter, professor of economics at Harvard School of Economics and author of the book on IBM.
