Patti LaBelle prosecuted for allegedly causing a young child to vomit out of fear
A New York family claims that Disco diva Patti LaBelle, who went on a rampage of violence in the lobby of their Manhattan apartment building, terrified their little girl to the point where she vomited out of fear.
The tirade of the singer "Lady Marmalade" frightened the little Genevieve Monk aged 18 months, so much so that she suffered "personality changes, sleep disorders" and "increased fear of strangers", says her family during the trial of the Supreme Court of Manhattan.
