Austria is thus responding to a request made by the summit of euro zone member countries in Brussels on 26th October last: the heads of State and government then demanded that the reduction of public deficits and a return to balance of public accounts be included by the end of 2012 in the constitution or in a law of equal value.
The system adopted by the Austrian government is close to the "German model", Germany having been the first European country to adopt such a "rule".
By 2017 the structural public deficit will have to decrease each year by 0.75% of the GDP and from 2017 the structural public deficit of the Federal State will not have to exceed 0.35% of the GDP each year, whilst the regional states as well as the municipalities will have to present balanced budgets.
The aim is to bring public debt below the 60% criterion set by the Maastricht Treaty by 2020/21.
